1 clove Garlic
1 tablespoon Italian Seasoning
1.5 ounce Tomato Paste
8 ounce Pre-Cooked Turkey Meatballs
2 unit Demi-Baguette
½ cup Mozzarella Cheese
2 ounce Mixed Greens
1.5 ounce Italian Dressing
Salt
Pepper
1 teaspoon Olive Oil
½ teaspoon Sugar
3 tablespoon Butter

• Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.   • Peel and mince or grate garlic.  • Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large pan over medium high heat. Add half the garlic; cook, stirring, until fragrant, 30 seconds. • Stir in tomato paste and half the Italian Seasoning (all for 4 servings). Cook, stirring, until combined. • Add meatballs*, ½ tsp sugar, salt, pepper, and ½ cup water. (For 4, use 1 tsp sugar and 1 cup water.) Cook, stirring, until sauce is slightly thickened and meatballs are warmed through, 1-2 minutes.  • Stir in 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4) and turn off heat.

• In a small microwave-safe bowl, combine 2 TBSP butter (4 TBSP for 4 servings) and remaining garlic; season with salt and pepper. Microwave until butter is just softened, 10-15 seconds.  • Slice baguettes lengthwise, stopping before you get all the way through; spread cut sides with garlic butter. Place cut sides up on a baking sheet. • Toast on middle rack of oven until lightly browned, 2-3 minutes.  • Carefully fill toasted baguettes with meatballs and sauce, then sprinkle with mozzarella. • Return to middle rack until cheese melts, 2-3 minutes more.

• Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, toss mixed greens with Italian dressing until evenly coated. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

• Divide subs and salad between plates. Serve